<font color="#FF0000">WINGMAN</font><br>
<tt>Tue Aug 12  1:43:51 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Mustang Two Four<br><br>
A man of honor and humility is always welcome on my wing.  The strength of a warrior is not always in the winning a battle, but in his ability to take learned lessons to the next battle.  It takes great courage for a man to rise from his own ashes.  The strongest metals are only tempered in the hottest fires and we have spent our time in hell.<br><br>
I watched my own co-pilot accept death before I was ready and cease to fight.  With complete serinity he waited for the end.  Something I have yet to understand.  I brought him back a shattered man never to fly again.  One of a thousand experiences I will never forget.<br><br>
We will survive, of that I am sure.  Of more interest to me is your uncompromising willingness to carry the burdens of so many allowing each to feel their self worth.  A warrior who has evolved into a chief I presume.<br><br>
I followed intently the running battle with the Doc.  I was not confused by your change of method.  I was only suprised because it took so long.  I must admit many will have to wait and see.  I admire you for taking the risk to see if the Doc is honest with himself and the members of the site.<br><br>
You have seeded the fertile ground.  The path we will all have to walk extracts its own price which we will gladly pay.<br><br>

<p><code>--   (Silent Warrior) </code><p>


